==Demographics==
As of the 2000 census,<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> there were 2,150 people, 843 households, and 558 families living in the borough. The population density was {{convert|2,690.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 870 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,088.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the borough was 97.77% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.84% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.23% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.23% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.28% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.65% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.88% of the population.

